text.section:
If the charter prohibits the issuance of acquired shares, the number of authorized shares is reduced by the number of shares acquired, effective upon the filing with the Department of articles supplementary which shall set forth:
The name of the corporation;
The number of outstanding shares of stock of the corporation that have been acquired by the corporation and that by their terms may not be reissued, and the class and series of the shares;
The number of authorized shares of the corporation remaining after the acquisition of outstanding shares, itemized by class and series; and
The fact that no amendment to the charter is effected by the articles supplementary, their sole purpose being to record the reduction of authorized shares resulting from the acquisition of shares that by the terms of the existing charter may not be reissued.
